## Developer Guide

If you are new to using `nbdev` here are some useful pointers to get you
started.

### Install semisupervised_learning in Development mode

``` sh
# make sure semisupervised_learning package is installed in development mode
$ pip install -e .

# make changes under nbs/ directory
# ...

# compile to have changes apply to semisupervised_learning
$ nbdev_prepare
```

## Usage

### Installation

Install latest from the GitHub
[repository](https://github.com/HasanGoni/semisupervised_learning):

``` sh
$ pip install git+https://github.com/HasanGoni/semisupervised_learning.git
```

or from [conda](https://anaconda.org/HasanGoni/semisupervised_learning)

``` sh
$ conda install -c HasanGoni semisupervised_learning
```

or from [pypi](https://pypi.org/project/semisupervised_learning/)

``` sh
$ pip install semisupervised_learning
```

### Documentation

Documentation can be found hosted on this GitHub

Additionally you can find package manager specific guidelines on
